<h2 id="sectionTitle" class="sectionTitle">Fun In The Sun</h2>
<div id="activity" class="laJollaShores">
    <img src="laJollaShores.jpg" alt="La Jolla Shores">
    <div id="activityTitle" class="activityTitle">La Jolla Shores</div>
    <div id="activityDetails"><a href="https://maps.app.goo.gl/umWERCsRmaqot8gFA">Parking Location</a></div>
    <div id="activityDetails"></div>
    <div id="activityDetails"><p>Before parking, or after, head into town and rent some snorkel gear (walking distance)<br>
                                Once on the beach, walk to the south end and head into the water. If you are a strong swimmer, or the tide is not too crazy, you can swim all the way to the coves.<br>
                                There are also guided tours by kayak that will take you out to the coves and into a cave if the tide is right!<br>
                                In the warmer months, there will be a high chance for observing the non aggressive leopard sharks! They are the reason I own my own snorkel gear!</p></div>
</div>
<div id="activity" class="anniesSlotCanyon">
    <img src="anniesSlotCanyon.jpg" alt="Annies Slot Canyon">
    <div id="activityTitle" class="activityTitle">Annie's Slot Canyon</div>
    <div id="activityDetails"><a href="https://maps.app.goo.gl/f8kmMya3dkL6msv67">Parking Location</a></div>
    <div id="activityDetails"></div>
    <div id="activityDetails"><p>Just down right beautiful and fun for the whole family!<br> 
                                My wife and I love the water side stroll to get to the slots.<br>
                                We usually go through the slots twice before heading back.<br>
                                If you would like to explore a not very populated beach afterwards, head to <a href="https://maps.app.goo.gl/eb1YKtvsbSWa2eQc7"> this</a> spot.
    </p></div>
</div>
<div id="activity" class="missionBaySportcenter">
    <img src="mBSC.jpg" alt="Mission Bay Sportenter">
    <div id="activityTitle" class="activityTitle">Mission Bay Sportcenter</div>
    <div id="activityDetails"><a href="https://maps.app.goo.gl/UkGUwfM4Rh1w2nyy9">Location</a></div>
    <div id="activityDetails"></div>
    <div id="activityDetails"><p>I have fully enjoyed finding this place! From stand up paddle boards, to jet skis, or even my favorite choice, a sail boat!<br>
                                Experience sailing is not needed. In fact, you will find it surprising how incredibly quick you pick it up!<br>
                                For a low cost, you can rent a sail boat and have all of mission bay covered in less than an hour.</p></div>
</div>
<div id="activity" class="safariAnimalPark">
    <img src="safariAnimalPArk.jpg" alt="The Waterin Hole">
    <div id="activityTitle" class="activityTitle">Safari Animal Park</div>
    <div id="activityDetails"><a href="https://maps.app.goo.gl/pSg6Yb3eV9AyKqcP9">Location</a></div>
    <div id="activityDetails"></div>
    <div id="activityDetails"><p>For zoo lovers, this place is great! You will be in the sun, so don't forget your sun block, a hat, and water!<br>
                                Aside from the animals, and the safari tram guide, I hope you are lucky enough to visit on a day that The Watering Hole is open.<br>
                                The picture above shows the dining area overlooking the field where you can see a variety of animals grazing on grass as you graze on your delicious meal.</p></div>
</div>
<div id="activity" class="CoronadoFerryLanding">
    <img src="coronadoFerryLanding.jpg" alt="Coronado Ferry Landing">
    <div id="activityTitle" class="activityTitle">Coronado Ferry Landing</div>
    <div id="activityDetails"><a href="https://maps.app.goo.gl/U8jWi7kHYGkQyJ7K8">Prefered Location</a></div>
    <div id="activityDetails"></div>
    <div id="activityDetails"><p>Just because the sun is down, does not mean your day needs to be over!<br>
                                The ferry landing has been for many years one of my favorite night spots for taking in the view of Downtown, or even a nice stroll in the night air.<br>
                                If you would like to get a little more out of the experience check out the ferry <a href="https://www.flagshipsd.com/ferry-routes/broadway-pier"> schedule</a> and book a round trip.<br>
                                 </p></div>
</div>
<div id="activity" class="coronadoBeach">
    <img src="coronadoBeach.jpg" alt="Hotel Del">
    <div id="activityTitle" class="activityTitle">Coronado Beach</div>
    <div id="activityDetails"><a href="https://maps.app.goo.gl/sSLtyjKsaYmUgz9Q7">Prefered Location</a></div>
    <div id="activityDetails"></div>
    <div id="activityDetails"><p>More after sun down serenity! Walk the beach at night to the sounds of the waves crashing at your side.<br>
                                If you get lucky, you may stumble upon the military running training near and in the water!<br>
                                Observe the historic <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hotel_del_Coronado"> Hotel Del</a> lit up in the distance as you draw closer to it. You can even walk through it and appreciate this architectural beauty! </p></div>
</div>
